div.p: Use git to clone the project. 16GB of ram and some type of CUDA compatible GPU is recommended for running the project

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 9px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; max-height: 87px; max-width: 150px; width: 150px; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

div.p: Download WebOfScience.zip folder, get the Data.xlsx file under /Metadata/ in the archive, copy it as WOS.xlsx under /Data/ in the project

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 9px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; max-height: 87px; max-width: 150px; width: 150px; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

div.p: Download part1,2,and 3.zip, place part1,2,and 3 folders in those zip files under /Data/NSF Dataset in the project directory

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 9px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; max-height: 87px; max-width: 150px; width: 150px; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

div.div: Retrieve the dataset using metha OAI harvester, copy all of the retrieved xml files into /Data/ARXIV in the project directory

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 9px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; max-height: 87px; max-width: 150px; width: 150px; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

div.p: Run parse.py under each folder in /Parsing/ in the project directory. Recommended to have 16GB of ram to do this for ARXIV

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 9px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; max-height: 87px; max-width: 150px; width: 150px; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

p.font: For each folder in /Featurizing/ in the project directory, run getUnigramFeatures.py, getBigramFeatures.py, and featurize.py in that order

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 9px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; max-height: 87px; max-width: 150px; width: 150px; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

div.p: For the folders /NB/,/DNN/, /MaxEnt/ under /Models/ in the project, run all train.py to train the Naive Bayes, Deep Neural Net, and MaxEnt models respectively
